com.gnostice.pdfone
Interface CleanUpOptions

public interface CleanUpOptions

Defines Clean-Up options to specify what needs to be updated/removed when a PDF operation is performed. Eg. when PdfDocument#deletePages(String, int) is performed the CleanUpOptions can be specified {@link CleanUpOptions} such as {@link CleanUpOptions#UPDATE_AFFECTED_LINK_ANNOTATION_ACTIONS} to specify if affected actions of the Link annotations on the other pages should be removed if they are having GoTo actions that are pointing to the deleting pages and updated if they are having GoTo actions that are pointing to the other pages according to the changing page order.

Field Summary
static int ALL
          Specifies all Clean-Up options of CleanUpOptions should be performed.
static int NONE
          Specifies none of the Clean-Up options of CleanUpOptions should be performed.
static int REMOVE_AFFECTED_EMPTY_LINK_ANNOTATIONS
          Specifies if the affected link annotations itself should be removed if they do not have any actions to be performed.
static int UPDATE_AFFECTED_LINK_ANNOTATION_ACTIONS
          Specifies if affected actions of the Link annotations of the intended pages should be updated/removed.
